#############################################
# 	CBC Mode Feistel Decryption
# 	
# 	Description:
# 	This program decrypts ciphertext blocks using a simple Feistel network 
# 	in Cipher Block Chaining (CBC) mode.
#
# 	Parameters:
# 	Given: 
# 	- ciphertext: Contains encrypted data (pre encrypted text using same algorithm ) , (512 block, 1000 word)
# 	- iv: Initialization Vector for CBC mode (2 words)
# 	- key: The encryption key used in Feistel rounds (1 word)
# 	- numBlocks: Number of encrypted blocks (1000)
# 	- numRounds: Number of Feistel rounds per block (150)
# 	Output: 
# 	- decrypted: Memory space for storing decrypted output
#
# 	Register Usage:
# 	- $8: Pointer to ciphertext block
# 	- $9: Pointer to decrypted text block
# 	- $10, $11: IV (Initialization Vector) for CBC mode
# 	- $12: Number of Feistel rounds
# 	- $13: Number of blocks to decrypt
# 	- $14: Left half of ciphertext block
# 	- $15: Encryption key
# 	- $16: Right half of ciphertext block
# 	- $20: Temporary register for Feistel function
# 	- $23: Register for Feistel transformation
# 	- $24, $25: Store previous ciphertext block (used as IV for next block)
# 	- $26: Round counter
#  Important related to differences in addresing modes:
# to test on your cpu, you need to replace the addresses labels with the starting address depending on the addresing mode:
# for example : if byte addresable replace  lw $11, iv+4($0)   with lw $11, 8($0) , (iv address =  4) and 4+4 = 8
# also you need to replace some values depending on your addressing mode , check line 87, 100, 137, 146 comments
#
#           word addresable: 
# starting addresses in modelsim memory :
# key        --> 0
# IV         --> 1
# cyphertext --> 3
# decrypted  --> 2003
#
#
#
#
#
#           byte addresable: 
# starting addresses in modelsim memory :
# key        --> 0
# IV         --> 4
# cyphertext --> 12
# decrypted  --> 8012
#
#############################################

